            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="x-oldsun-Latn">
                 <!-- note on edition: 1. ḥ > h, 2 paten (·) are deleted, 3. ṁ > ṅ, 4. ṁṅ > ṅ -->
	<p><pb ed="#A" n="1v"/>ndah nihan varahakna saṅ sadu, 
<app><lem wit="#A">de</lem><rdg wit="#B">den</rdg></app> saṅ mamet hayu, 
hana ta 
<app><lem type="conj" source="bib:Atja+SalehDanasasmita1981_03">saṅ hyaṅ</lem><rdg wit="A"><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/><seg type="component" subtype="body"><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="component"/></seg>yaṁ</rdg><rdg wit="#B"><gap reason="lost"/></rdg></app> siksa kandaṅ karəsian ṅaranya, 
kayatnakna voṅ sakabeh, ujar saṅ sadu, ṅagəlarkәn saṅ hyaṅ siksa kandaṅ karәsian,</p>
                <p>ini saṅ hyaṅ dasa-krәta, kundaṅən uraṅ reya, 
<app><lem>asiṅ nu dek</lem><rdg wit="#A"><unclear>Asiṁ nu dek·</unclear></rdg><rdg type="lacune" wit="#B"/></app> <app><lem type="norm">na<reg>ñj</reg>ərkən</lem><rdg wit="#A">najərkən</rdg><rdg wit="#B"><gap reason="lost"/></rdg></app>
 saṅ hyaṅ sasana krəta, pakənən hәbәl hirup həbəl 
<app><lem type="emn">ñovana</lem><rdg wit="#A #B">ñavana</rdg></app>, 
<app><lem type="norm">jadian</lem><rdg wit="#A">jadyan</rdg><rdg wit="#B"><gap reason="lost"/></rdg></app><!-- Aditia: maybe apply <reg> to dia or only to i; add this type of case to your list of normalizations --> kuras <app><lem type="emn">jadian</lem><rdg wit="#A">jadya</rdg></app><!-- Adita: what about B? --><!-- or spelling jadyan? is jadya[n] tahun the same phenomenon as ṅa[ñ]jĕrkĕn? --> tahun dәgdәg tajәr 
<app><lem type="emn">jaya</lem><rdg wit="#A">ya</rdg><rdg wit="#B"><gap reason="lost"/></rdg></app> praṅ, ñovana na 
 <app><lem wit="#B">uraṅ</lem><rdg wit="#A"><unclear>U</unclear>raṁ</rdg></app><!-- Aditia: do we need this app entry? --> reya,</p>
                <p><app><lem wit="#B">ini</lem><rdg wit="#A"><gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="1"/>ni</rdg></app> 
<app><lem wit="#A">byaktana</lem><rdg wit="#B">byitana</rdg></app> saṅ hyaṅ <app><lem wit="A">dasa-krәta</lem><rdg wit="#B">dasakrata</rdg></app> ṅaranya, kalaṅkaṅ saṅ hyaṅ dasa-<app><lem wit="#A">sila</lem><rdg wit="#B"><lacunaStart/></rdg></app>, maya-maya saṅ hyaṅ dasa-marga, kaprәtyaksaan na dasa-indriya, pakәn ṅrәtakәn <app><lem wit="#A">di</lem><rdg source="Atja+Danasasmita1981_03"/></app> bumi lamba, di bumi <app><lem type="emn">parәk</lem><rdg wit="#A">paR̥<unclear>ka</unclear></rdg></app>,</p> 
                <p>ini pakәn uraṅ ṅrәtakәn bumi  
<app><lem type="emn">lamba<!-- Aditia: do you want to use <reg> around mb? -->, caaṅ jalan</lem><rdg source="Atja+Danasasmita1981_03">lamba caaṅ jalan</rdg><rdg wit="#A">la<unclear>mbha</unclear><gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="3"/>ṁ<unclear>ja</unclear>lan·</rdg>
</app> 
pañjaṅ tajur, paka pradana, liñih pipir <app><lem type="emn" source="Atja+Danasasmita1981_03">caaṅ</lem><rdg wit="#A"><unclear>ca</unclear>A</rdg></app> bu<pb n="A2r"/>ruan,</p>
                 <p>a<supplied reason="nonstandard">ṅ</supplied>gәs ma imah kaәsi, lәit kaәsi, parañje kaәsi, huma kaomean, sadapan karaksa, palana ta hurip hirup sovera varas, ñovana <app><lem type="emn">saṅ mavaṅsa rat</lem><rdg wit="#A">saṁ mavaṁ rat·</rdg><rdg source="Atja+SalehDanasasmita1981_03">sama vaṅ <supplied reason="unknown">sa</supplied>rat</rdg></app>, saṅkilaṅ di lamba, trәna taru lata guluma, hejo lembok tumuvuh sarba pala vovohan dadi na <app><lem wit="#A">hudan</lem><rdg source="Atja+Danasasmita1981_01">hujan</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#A">landuh</lem><rdg source="Atja+Danasasmita1981_01"></rdg></app> tahun tumuvuh daek maka hurip na uraṅ reya</p>
                 <p>iña eta saṅ hyaṅ sasana krәta, di lamba ṅarana,</p> 
                <p>ini saṅ hyaṅ dasa-krәta, nu dipajarkәn kalaṅkaṅ saṅ hyaṅ dasa-sila ta, ya maya maya saṅ hyaṅ dasa-marga ta, kaprәtyaksaan na dasa-indriya,</p>

